VARIANCE QUERY STRUCTURE — TWO QUERIES:
For ALL variance questions, generate TWO queries.

QUERY ROUTING — TWO PARTS. Apply both.

PART A — QUERY SUBJECT TYPE (determines answer table):
Condition 1 — Specific Product (user names a specific product e.g. "Treasury and Risk", "Front Arena"):
  -> Q1 GROUP BY "l9_account" (L7 account breakdown) with product filter
  -> State product total first in response

Condition 2 — Top N Products (user asks "top N products"):
  -> If product level stated -> Q1 GROUP BY that level
  -> If product level not stated -> Q1 GROUP BY "l6_description" (default)

Condition 3 — Specific Client (user names a specific client):
  -> Q1 GROUP BY "l7_description" (L7 product) WHERE entity_name = that client

Condition 4 — Top N Clients (user asks "top N clients"):
  -> Q1 GROUP BY "entity_name"

Condition 5 — Account only (no product or client filter):
  -> Q1 GROUP BY "l9_account" (L7 account)

PART B — QUESTION TYPE OVERLAY (determines source table and key takeaway order):
Q-Type RUC ("ruc", "revenue under contract"):
  -> Q1 GROUP BY "l6_description" WHERE "ruc_risk"='RUC' AND attrition IS NULL
  -> Key takeaways order: 1. RUC breakdown 2. l6_description 3. entity_name

Q-Type Risk ("risk", "risk id", "risk uid"):
  -> Q1 GROUP BY "ruc_risk" (showing Risk ID vs Risk UID split)
  -> Key takeaways order: 1. Risk ID vs UID 2. l6_description 3. entity_name

Q-Type Attrition ("attrition"):
  -> Q1 GROUP BY "attrition_description"
  -> Key takeaways order: 1. attrition_description 2. l6_description 3. entity_name

Q-Type Variance/Comparison (default when no Part B keyword):
  -> Apply Part A conditions above

COMBINED ROUTING TABLE:
"customer","client","entity" + no Part B      -> Condition 3 or 4 from Part A
"ruc","organic"                               -> Part B Q-Type RUC -> GROUP BY "l6_description"
"risk"                                        -> Part B Q-Type Risk -> GROUP BY "ruc_risk"
"attrition"                                   -> Part B Q-Type Attrition -> GROUP BY "attrition_description"
"account","recurring","non-recurring"         -> Condition 5 Part A -> GROUP BY "l9_account"
specific product name in colvalue_mapping     -> Condition 1 Part A -> GROUP BY "l9_account" with product filter
"top N products" / no specific product        -> Condition 2 Part A -> GROUP BY "l6_description"
"comparison"/"variance" with no other filter  -> Condition 5 Part A -> GROUP BY "l9_account"

